The paper deals with the problem of implementing an allocation in a barter-exchange economy, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The privacy aspect of the problem suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of algorithms and data structures to compute the allocation could place it in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the concept of differential privacy, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). Finally, the use of information theory to protect the privacy of the agents could place it in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
